              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The mass-identifying telescope",
                "consisted of a combination of a 74-mu-m-thick x",
                "100-mm2-area, surface-barrier diode and a 3000-mu-m-",
                "thick x 200-mm2 area Si(Li) diode."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For singles and for pg-coincidence gamma-ray",
                "counting a 35-cm3 true coaxial Ge(Li) detector was",
                "used, which had a resolution of 2.2 keV full width at",
                "half maximum at 1332 keV. For gg-coincidence counting",
                "a second 30-cm3 Ge(Li) detector with a 2.8-keV",
                "resolution at 1332 keV was also employed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were self-supporting 58Ni foils (enriched",
                "to 99.95% in mass 58) and were prepared by rolling of",
                "the metal. The target thicknesses were between 0.5",
                "and 2.0 mg/cm2."
              ]
            },
